\ shift-with with no resume unwinds to the reset, leaving interp->unwinding
\ set. At the top level that unwind escapes without being cleared, and since
\ no error_flag is set, the REPL recovery block never runs -- so every later
\ line silently no-ops (DISPATCH / run_inner bail while unwinding). Clearing
\ unwinding unconditionally per line breaks the wedge: the line after the
\ trigger must still execute. Without the fix the 42 below never prints.
reset [: 99 . cr :] shift-with
42 . cr
